ITV.Tour.de.France.2014.Stage.7.Highlights.PDTV.x264-NX

Friday 11th July 2014 ITV4
7pm to 8pm Highlights

Highlights from stage seven, a long one for the peloton as they cross the 234.5km between Epernay and Nancy. With two category four climbs in the run-up, the distance is not the only factor that will make this stage hard to control. The last climb, the Cote de Boufflers, hits gradients of 8 per cent and is a mere 5km from the line promising an intense finale. Presented by Gary Imlach with analysis from Chris Boardman, commentary by Phil Liggett and Paul Sherwen with Ned Boulting the reporter at the roadside.
